# Strategic Strategy: Modularize & Audit (Build 1101E)

This plan shifts our focus to **Modularization (Refactoring)** as the primary priority. By splitting large files into smaller, focused modules, we reduce "Context Noise" and allow AI agents (like Opus 4.6) to perform deeper forensic audits with higher accuracy.

## Proposed Changes

### [Phase 1: UI Modularization]
Split [UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.cs) (~2246 lines) into:
- `UI.IPC.cs`: TCP Server, Client Handlers, and [ProcessIpcCommands](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.cs#406-1163).
- `UI.Compliance.cs`: Compliance Hub, P/L tracking, and Daily Summary logic.
- `UI.Sizing.cs`: ATR Auto-Sizing Engine and Position Sizing math.
- `UI.Callbacks.cs`: Hotkeys and Chart Click handlers.

### [Phase 2: Order Modularization]
Split [UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs) (~2024 lines) into:
- `Orders.Callbacks.cs`: [OnOrderUpdate](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs#37-530), [OnPositionUpdate](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs#636-737), and [OnAccountOrderUpdate](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs#531-635).
- `Orders.Management.cs`: [SubmitBracketOrders](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs#738-814), [CleanupPosition](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs#1378-1456), and [ReconcileOrphanedOrders](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs#1888-2019).
- `Orders.Actions.cs`: Hotkey execution logic (ExecuteLong, ExecuteShort, Flatten).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- **Compilation Check**: Run `F5` in NinjaTrader after each module split to ensure namespaces and `partial class` references are intact.

### Manual Verification
- **Agent Audit**: Hand one small module (e.g., `UI.Sizing.cs`) to **Opus 4.6** and ask it to find edge cases.
- **Result**: Compare finding density before vs. after refactor.
